text.tspan: Sidebar Button
toggles the visibility of the Sidebar
Toolbox Sidebar
The Toolbox can only display one item, list or form at once.
To solve this, any of these are arranged in frames. This idead
was inspired by the organisation multiple Tabs in common
web browsers and the screens seen at the Apple iPhone.
You can navigate through the open frames with the History
found in the Sidebar.
History
represents the frames currently
present in the Toolbox.
click one to go to this frame without
destroying the currenty shown one.
Switch Clipboard / History
only on of both can be shown at once, so
you have to toggle between them.
Clipboard
the Clipboard takes any Item you can
drag and keeps it for later use. It
belongs to you, no one else can see it.
If you create a new Item somewhere,
it will be added to your Clipboard.
Remove Button
every Item in the Clipboard has a Button to remove it.
It won't be destroyed, but it won't show up in your
Clipboard anymore - until you possibly drag it there later
Switch Clipboard / History
notice that after switching the colors
of the buttons have changed
